&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role: What&#39;s in the Box&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;We are looking for a Culinary Intern for our fast growing product team in Amsterdam. Working on the culinary team, you provide recipe testing support and give tasting feedback to help shape the meals customers receive every week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Factor is a quickly growing brand within the HelloFresh Group. With ambitious product expansion plans, our culinary team is testing and launching multiple new meals every week from our test kitchen in the Amsterdam office. We’re seeking a Culinary Intern with a passion for food to help us accelerate this growth and delight our customers with delicious and healthy new recipes. On a small and dynamic team, this role has the opportunity to have a significant impact on our weekly menu and customer experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do: The Recipe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize test kitchen ingredients, placing reorders when inventory is low, shopping weekly fresh items, and supporting R&amp;amp;D chefs with ingredient prep for recipe testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test assigned recipes, cooking components of meals and presenting them at team tastings. Document feedback and update recipes in development tool&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure recipe accuracy and completeness for newly onboarded meals and existing recipes, updating and cross-checking as needed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take on the challenge of creating structure and clear processes within a large amount of product content across multiple languages and markets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and be supported in strengthening your communication and presentation skills, while working on cross-functional team projects with different (international) personalities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a structured way of working and&amp;nbsp; support the product department in coordinating their administrative tasks, and documenting the processes created.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring: The Ingredients&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interested in culinary product development&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You don’t shy away from uncertainty and know to perform in a fast-pace environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility and adaptability to changing priorities, tasks, and work environments are essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paying close attention to details and maintaining accuracy in tasks is important for maintaining accurate product information and preventing errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re proactive, ambitious, and make things happen - just like the rest of the team!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
